PARLIAMENT - President Cyril Ramaphosa will respond to members of parliaments' debate over the State of the Nation Address on Thursday. The National Assembly and the National Council of Provinces held a joint sitting to debate President Cyril Ramaphosa's State of the Nation Address on Tuesday and Wednesday. The debate was highly eventful with Julius Malema and other EFF Members of Parliament leaving the joint sitting on Tuesday after accusations of domestic violence were levelled against political leaders. A fight nearly broke out in Parliament after Malema accused Ramaphosa of beating his former wife, Nomazizi Mtshotshisa.